1
00:01:32,820 --> 00:01:35,900
[Light to the Night]

2
00:01:37,340 --> 00:01:42,300
[1997]

3
00:01:47,100 --> 00:01:50,260
[Qihuang Clinic]

4
00:02:10,460 --> 00:02:13,460
[Light to the Night]
[Episode 3]

5
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:16,300
That person also told me

6
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,300
that in the afternoon of June 30th,

7
00:02:19,590 --> 00:02:20,650
those two people would head

8
00:02:20,670 --> 00:02:21,410
to Qihuang Clinic.

9
00:02:22,390 --> 00:02:23,460
He told me to wait for them there.

10
00:02:24,870 --> 00:02:25,300
A clinic?

11
00:02:25,430 --> 00:02:26,850
An unlicensed qigong center.

12
00:02:27,270 --> 00:02:28,220
It's probably sealed.

13
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:29,940
What about the photo?

14
00:02:30,270 --> 00:02:32,090
I burned it.

15
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:34,370
It's a rule in the gang.

16
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:38,340
What does make them disappear mean?

17
00:02:38,830 --> 00:02:40,130
Kill them?

18
00:02:40,270 --> 00:02:42,170
I don't know either.

19
00:02:42,190 --> 00:02:43,690
He picked up the phone call

20
00:02:43,690 --> 00:02:44,810
and vanished.

21
00:02:46,270 --> 00:02:47,300
Officer He.

22
00:02:47,870 --> 00:02:49,900
I never intended to kill anyone.

23
00:02:50,270 --> 00:02:51,810
I just wanted to scare them

24
00:02:52,040 --> 00:02:52,850
so they would

25
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:53,810
leave Weiyang

26
00:02:53,830 --> 00:02:55,060
and never come back again.

27
00:02:55,480 --> 00:02:57,090
That's disappearing, isn't it?

28
00:02:58,200 --> 00:03:00,130
I waited and waited,

29
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:01,390
but no one ever came.

30
00:03:02,110 --> 00:03:03,690
So, I went out to take a peek.

31
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:06,530
Then, I heard screams

32
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:08,370
on the floor above.

33
00:03:08,830 --> 00:03:10,370
I then realized that the woman and the old man

34
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:11,780
didn't head to the 17th floor,

35
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:13,250
but the 18th floor.

36
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:15,940
I went to Pattia before.

37
00:03:16,590 --> 00:03:18,310
I know there is a secret door there.

38
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:19,500
I figured they

39
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:21,090
might be hiding on the rooftop.

40
00:03:21,670 --> 00:03:22,620
But I walked around

41
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:24,020
and didn't see them.

42
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:25,570
Who gave you the keys?

43
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:29,130
I used some tricks.

44
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:33,500
Then, I wanted to get out of there.

45
00:03:36,110 --> 00:03:37,900
Then you people came to the 18th floor,

46
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:39,160
group

47
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:40,120
by group.

48
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:42,590
I couldn't run away.

49
00:03:45,430 --> 00:03:47,470
I waited until the sun set.

50
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:52,460
I couldn't stand it anymore.

51
00:03:52,990 --> 00:03:54,090
So, I let it out.

52
00:03:54,990 --> 00:03:56,620
I was all sweaty and dirty,

53
00:03:57,590 --> 00:03:58,620
and I thought

54
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:00,060
I couldn't just

55
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,460
suffer this for nothing.

56
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:03,740
I must get the balance of the payment.

57
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:06,500
I must show the gang how good I am.

58
00:04:12,710 --> 00:04:15,020
So, I bluffed.

59
00:04:15,870 --> 00:04:16,860
I grabbed a bag,

60
00:04:17,080 --> 00:04:18,330
made myself a bloody cloak,

61
00:04:19,830 --> 00:04:21,370
and told everyone that I had killed two people.

62
00:04:28,320 --> 00:04:28,810
Then,

63
00:04:28,830 --> 00:04:29,770
the blood in the bag...

64
00:04:29,790 --> 00:04:30,660
It's all chicken blood.

65
00:04:31,350 --> 00:04:32,690
Test it if you don't trust me.

66
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:34,210
If it's human blood,

67
00:04:34,230 --> 00:04:35,620
just shoot me on the spot.

68
00:04:46,230 --> 00:04:47,570
What were you doing in 407?

69
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:53,810
Who gave you the job?

70
00:04:55,350 --> 00:04:55,810
I don't know who he is.

71
00:04:56,830 --> 00:04:57,540
How much did he offer?

72
00:04:57,760 --> 00:04:59,370
40,000 yuan.

73
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:01,500
But he still owes me the balance of 30,000 yuan.

74
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:03,420
You can't even recognize him.

75
00:05:03,930 --> 00:05:05,250
How are you supposed to ask him to pay?

76
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:06,690
He said

77
00:05:06,710 --> 00:05:08,700
he'd call me after the job.

78
00:05:08,910 --> 00:05:09,690
Buddy.

79
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:12,010
You killed them.

80
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:14,620
Why would he contact you?

81
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:15,620
So that you

82
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:16,250
can turn yourself in

83
00:05:16,270 --> 00:05:17,180
to the police?

84
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:20,420
Gosh.

85
00:05:22,910 --> 00:05:23,960
Did anyone see you

86
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,130
when you did it?

87
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:29,540
Answer me!

88
00:05:31,390 --> 00:05:32,330
I think

89
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:38,300
I saw someone when I was leaving.

90
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:39,130
You think?

91
00:05:55,950 --> 00:05:56,560
Idiot!

92
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,810
And you can sleep at night like this?

93
00:05:58,150 --> 00:05:59,130
Find that witness

94
00:05:59,350 --> 00:06:00,330
and silence him.

95
00:06:00,710 --> 00:06:02,690
That old man in 407

96
00:06:02,710 --> 00:06:03,840
saw me.

97
00:06:04,790 --> 00:06:05,890
I had to silence him.

98
00:06:06,790 --> 00:06:09,010
Someone still owes me 30,000 yuan.

99
00:06:09,350 --> 00:06:10,890
If someone tells the police,

100
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:13,060
I will be busted.

101
00:06:13,590 --> 00:06:15,570
I was very polite to him.

102
00:06:16,590 --> 00:06:17,770
Yes.

103
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:20,180
He was quite polite.

104
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,810
But really, I've never seen him before.

105
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:24,370
Never.

106
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:26,300
Last night,

107
00:06:26,910 --> 00:06:29,250
I was reading a detective novel in my bed.

108
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:31,250
I was captivated by it,

109
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:33,060
and it kept me up.

110
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:33,980
I couldn't sleep,

111
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:36,330
so I thought I could climb some stairs

112
00:06:36,350 --> 00:06:37,180
and sweat a little

113
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:38,370
before I went to bed.

114
00:06:38,760 --> 00:06:41,130
As soon as I opened the door to the staircase,

115
00:06:42,830 --> 00:06:45,660
I felt so drowsy.

116
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:46,810
My eyelids were heavy.

117
00:06:46,830 --> 00:06:48,010
I could barely keep them open.

118
00:06:48,270 --> 00:06:49,860
So, I went back to sleep.

119
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,940
I didn't see anything.

120
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:53,980
I didn't see him.

121
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:57,620
You love to read detective novels?

122
00:06:58,230 --> 00:06:59,210
Yes.

123
00:06:59,230 --> 00:07:00,330
You too?

124
00:07:00,350 --> 00:07:00,890
Yes.

125
00:07:01,910 --> 00:07:03,690
We have the same hobby.

126
00:07:03,910 --> 00:07:05,210
What kind of detective novels?

127
00:07:05,230 --> 00:07:07,210
The classical European ones or...

128
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:09,180
Du Mandun.

129
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:11,860
If you didn't see Jin Manlang, why did you call the police?

130
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:15,300
I'm a fan of mysteries.

131
00:07:16,150 --> 00:07:17,210
Did you notice?

132
00:07:17,790 --> 00:07:19,300
Yesterday, someone disappeared

133
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:21,010
in a locked room on the 18th floor.

134
00:07:21,390 --> 00:07:23,210
Today, everyone is singing

135
00:07:23,230 --> 00:07:24,580
that nursery song.

136
00:07:24,910 --> 00:07:26,500
Isn't that just like the prelude

137
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:28,100
to a murder

138
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:29,460
in every detective novel?

139
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:31,830
Speak plainly, please.

140
00:07:32,210 --> 00:07:32,860
Continue.

141
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:33,570
I understand everything.

142
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,010
Okay. Listen.

143
00:07:35,590 --> 00:07:36,500
I thought

144
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:37,370
the whole thing

145
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:38,940
could never be this simple.

146
00:07:39,230 --> 00:07:40,090
At first...

147
00:07:40,090 --> 00:07:41,500
You didn't even see a shadow.

148
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:42,890
Who says I didn't see anything?

149
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:45,010
I saw her clearly.

150
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:47,660
I saw the woman twice.

151
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:50,540
I saw her carrying...

152
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:51,300
Like...

153
00:07:52,030 --> 00:07:52,980
Relax.

154
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,300
Tell us one by one.

155
00:07:57,080 --> 00:07:58,010
I first saw her

156
00:07:59,030 --> 00:08:01,570
in the morning several days ago.

157
00:08:02,390 --> 00:08:03,860
Right at the corner

158
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:05,500
of the staircase.

159
00:08:16,710 --> 00:08:18,300
The second time I saw her

160
00:08:18,910 --> 00:08:20,010
was yesterday.

161
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:22,810
I was playing gateball

162
00:08:22,830 --> 00:08:23,420
at the park

163
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:25,060
with Meng and Wang.

164
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:27,250
I saw the woman walking by

165
00:08:27,270 --> 00:08:29,000
while carrying an old man.

166
00:08:29,030 --> 00:08:30,940
She looked exactly like the woman

167
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:32,020
I had met on the staircase

168
00:08:32,040 --> 00:08:33,730
several days ago.

169
00:08:33,870 --> 00:08:35,210
Are you sure they were identical?

170
00:08:38,110 --> 00:08:39,300
Try to recall.

171
00:08:39,590 --> 00:08:40,490
Did anything stand out

172
00:08:40,510 --> 00:08:41,570
when you saw the woman?

173
00:08:42,630 --> 00:08:43,380
Anything that stood out?

174
00:08:43,630 --> 00:08:43,990
Yes.

175
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:56,840
She had medical patches

176
00:08:57,160 --> 00:08:58,300
on her wrists.

177
00:08:58,580 --> 00:08:59,260
Over here

178
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:00,450
and over here.

179
00:09:04,470 --> 00:09:05,810
These are probably

180
00:09:06,830 --> 00:09:08,660
marks left by medical patches.

181
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:13,420
It matches.

182
00:09:14,040 --> 00:09:15,330
How so?

183
00:09:15,830 --> 00:09:17,690
The medical patch has her name on it?

184
00:09:18,830 --> 00:09:20,020
This is an important lead.

185
00:09:20,250 --> 00:09:21,090
What kind of woman

186
00:09:21,110 --> 00:09:22,440
would use medical patches on her wrists?

187
00:09:22,590 --> 00:09:24,330
It must have something to do with her job.

188
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:26,810
That's just your opinion.

189
00:09:26,830 --> 00:09:27,970
I think

190
00:09:27,990 --> 00:09:29,810
she might have injured her wrists while she carried things.

191
00:09:29,830 --> 00:09:30,940
Or she might have a scar

192
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,090
that she didn't want anyone to see.

193
00:09:32,110 --> 00:09:33,410
The possibilities are endless.

194
00:09:33,410 --> 00:09:33,980
Yes.

195
00:09:33,980 --> 00:09:34,940
You're very right.

196
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:36,490
All these possibilities

197
00:09:36,510 --> 00:09:37,940
are possible clues in this murder.

198
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:39,810
Must you get us a murder case?

199
00:09:39,830 --> 00:09:41,730
Someone has hired a man to kill them.

200
00:09:41,750 --> 00:09:43,140
How is this not a murder?

201
00:09:44,510 --> 00:09:45,490
Officer,

202
00:09:46,350 --> 00:09:47,730
is this truly a murder?

203
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:04,310
We analyzed the blood

204
00:10:04,470 --> 00:10:05,570
in the bag and on the rooftop.

205
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:06,780
It's not human blood.

206
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:08,940
The saliva sample from the cigarette butt

207
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:10,020
matches Jin Manlang.

208
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:14,780
It seems like someone

209
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:16,020
has tried so hard for nothing.

210
00:10:16,680 --> 00:10:18,490
They probably hope the witnesses are lying

211
00:10:18,630 --> 00:10:20,020
so that they can continue investigating.

212
00:10:22,110 --> 00:10:23,540
I know they are not lying.

213
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:24,540
How do you know?

214
00:10:24,610 --> 00:10:26,020
Eyes are the window to your soul.

215
00:10:26,220 --> 00:10:27,810
If you look to the left when you speak,

216
00:10:27,830 --> 00:10:28,540
it means that you're recalling.

217
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:29,850
If you look to the right, it means you're making things up.

218
00:10:30,230 --> 00:10:32,090
When Jin Manlang and Mr. Du were speaking,

219
00:10:32,230 --> 00:10:33,690
they were looking to the left.

220
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:35,260
What about the photo?

221
00:10:36,830 --> 00:10:38,440
I burned it.

222
00:10:42,230 --> 00:10:43,420
I first saw her

223
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:48,420
in the...

224
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:50,090
They did not

225
00:10:50,110 --> 00:10:51,780
have the telltale sign of lying.

226
00:10:57,400 --> 00:10:58,570
Smarty pants

227
00:10:58,590 --> 00:10:59,380
who like to lecture.

228
00:10:59,560 --> 00:11:01,060
They did not lie,

229
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,020
but that doesn't mean

230
00:11:02,040 --> 00:11:03,060
the two missing people

231
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:04,260
are not in danger.

232
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:06,970
Can you two stop arguing?

233
00:11:08,470 --> 00:11:09,810
I analyzed everything in the box.

234
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:10,940
Nothing new.

235
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,540
Keep it or return it,

236
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:13,450
it's your call.

237
00:11:14,920 --> 00:11:15,900
I still have work to do.

238
00:11:37,140 --> 00:11:42,260
[Missing Person]
[2015]

239
00:12:04,990 --> 00:12:06,690
[Missing Person]
Why is this poster

240
00:12:06,710 --> 00:12:07,940
still here?

241
00:12:09,110 --> 00:12:10,300
Isn't it weird?

242
00:12:10,870 --> 00:12:12,300
Let me show you something weirder.

243
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:35,180
Does this look familiar to you?

244
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:41,020
Does this belong to

245
00:12:41,470 --> 00:12:42,330
Jin Manlang?

246
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:50,660
[Missing Person]

247
00:12:50,680 --> 00:12:51,610
I returned

248
00:12:51,630 --> 00:12:53,210
everything back then.

249
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:55,140
This mooncake box

250
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:56,300
belongs to Wolfie.

251
00:12:57,710 --> 00:12:59,300
[The Greek Coffin Mystery]
This detective novel

252
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:00,330
belongs to Du Mandun.

253
00:13:01,590 --> 00:13:03,420
Why are their things

254
00:13:03,920 --> 00:13:05,730
kept together in the same place?

255
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:08,540
And look at the poster.

256
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,660
The paper

257
00:13:10,680 --> 00:13:11,570
and the ink

258
00:13:11,590 --> 00:13:12,450
are both new.

259
00:13:14,870 --> 00:13:16,210
Weird, isn't it?

260
00:13:16,750 --> 00:13:17,730
It has been so many years.

261
00:13:19,630 --> 00:13:21,180
I never believed

262
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,300
that Yuanlongli is haunted.

263
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:25,690
Someone must be behind all of this.

264
00:13:58,630 --> 00:13:59,540
407.

265
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:01,610
Du Mandun's unit.

266
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:04,020
He moved out several months ago.

267
00:14:28,350 --> 00:14:29,380
So, it was all a false alarm.

268
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:34,810
Du Mandun moved out,

269
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:36,540
but he didn't take his books.

270
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:47,780
I remember

271
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:49,200
he was quite invested

272
00:14:49,400 --> 00:14:51,150
in the missing person case back then.

273
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:53,020
He even discussed some conspiracies

274
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:53,810
or locked rooms with you.

275
00:14:54,470 --> 00:14:55,020
Sir,

276
00:14:55,750 --> 00:14:57,090
ever since we set foot into Yuanlongli,

277
00:14:57,320 --> 00:14:59,210
you've been mentioning that particular case.

278
00:14:59,470 --> 00:15:01,090
What does it have to do with the missing kid?

279
00:15:01,920 --> 00:15:03,330
It has everything to do with it.

280
00:15:03,630 --> 00:15:04,540
They are both missing person cases.

281
00:15:04,830 --> 00:15:05,300
So?

282
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:08,330
So, we're looking for them.

283
00:15:09,630 --> 00:15:10,490
Sir,

284
00:15:10,920 --> 00:15:12,690
I came to Weiyang to write the lesson plan,

285
00:15:12,710 --> 00:15:13,780
and my schedule is tight enough.

286
00:15:16,230 --> 00:15:17,570
Three floors left.

287
00:15:18,110 --> 00:15:19,210
You gave me your word.

288
00:15:19,630 --> 00:15:21,060
Now keep your promise.

289
00:15:32,230 --> 00:15:32,810
Let's go.

290
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:34,450
Let's go.

291
00:15:44,620 --> 00:15:45,900
[Weiyang Public Security Bureau Nanshan Branch]

292
00:15:45,900 --> 00:15:49,300
[1997]

293
00:15:59,710 --> 00:16:00,730
I already signed.

294
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:01,610
Please sign it, too.

295
00:16:03,700 --> 00:16:05,340
[Criminal Case Registration Form]

296
00:16:05,510 --> 00:16:06,730
Since you always go to Qu Dahai,

297
00:16:06,750 --> 00:16:07,540
ask him to sign it.

298
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:09,140
He doesn't have the power.

299
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:11,900
Neither do I.

300
00:16:12,280 --> 00:16:13,020
Don't worry.

301
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:13,610
After you sign it,

302
00:16:13,630 --> 00:16:14,540
I'll be in charge of it.

303
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:16,330
You're a rookie. How can you be in charge of it?

304
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:18,970
Our priority now is not to file a case.

305
00:16:18,990 --> 00:16:20,730
It's to find those two people.

306
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:31,900
If you won't sign the registration form,

307
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:33,490
can you sign this?

308
00:16:33,490 --> 00:16:34,380
[Evidence Subpoena Request Form]

309
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:36,140
What is this?

310
00:16:36,830 --> 00:16:38,540
The woman used medical patches.

311
00:16:38,710 --> 00:16:39,300
I want

312
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:40,610
to check the hospital records

313
00:16:40,630 --> 00:16:41,490
to see if someone

314
00:16:41,510 --> 00:16:42,530
injured their wrists lately.

315
00:16:44,470 --> 00:16:45,180
You don't

316
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:46,610
have any real-life experience, do you?

317
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:48,060
Do you think they

318
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:50,300
will go to the hospital for a small injury like this?

319
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:52,540
Where else

320
00:16:52,830 --> 00:16:53,570
could she have gotten the patches?

321
00:16:53,750 --> 00:16:54,850
In a pharmacy.

322
00:16:54,870 --> 00:16:55,940
In a clinic.

323
00:16:56,110 --> 00:16:58,080
Many people are selling common medications.

324
00:16:58,440 --> 00:16:59,540
Following your method,

325
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:00,690
I can sign it,

326
00:17:00,710 --> 00:17:02,690
and you still won't find anything after years.

327
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:04,290
Then, how should we proceed?

328
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:05,290
Put up posters

329
00:17:05,510 --> 00:17:06,580
and wait on the bench?

330
00:17:06,710 --> 00:17:08,140
Are you lecturing me right now?

331
00:17:08,710 --> 00:17:09,490
At least I caught someone

332
00:17:09,510 --> 00:17:10,820
after waiting the whole day.

333
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:12,250
What did you find?

334
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:13,940
Chicken blood?

335
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:15,620
Duck blood can be added to a hotpot.

336
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:16,730
But chicken blood? It's useless.

337
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:17,820
Enough.

338
00:17:17,840 --> 00:17:18,420
Will you sign it or not?

339
00:17:18,420 --> 00:17:19,140
No!

340
00:17:24,360 --> 00:17:25,140
Criminal department.

341
00:17:25,510 --> 00:17:26,050
Dad!

342
00:17:29,030 --> 00:17:29,530
Yes.

343
00:17:29,710 --> 00:17:30,440
It's me.

344
00:17:31,640 --> 00:17:32,820
You haven't come back in so long.

345
00:17:33,070 --> 00:17:35,580
It's getting harder to see you now.

346
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:38,140
I'll come back soon.

347
00:17:38,550 --> 00:17:39,490
Again?

348
00:17:40,070 --> 00:17:41,380
Your soon

349
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:42,730
is getting absurdly long.

350
00:17:43,070 --> 00:17:44,290
Kiddo,

351
00:17:45,230 --> 00:17:47,290
I recently ran into a troublemaker.

352
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:48,820
He keeps pestering me.

353
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:51,180
Then, buy me a bottle of Coke.

354
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,620
Don't tell Mom.

355
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:54,140
Sure.

356
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:55,380
Wait.

357
00:17:55,680 --> 00:17:56,580
Mom wants to talk to you.

358
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:57,860
Xiaohe.

359
00:17:58,160 --> 00:17:59,010
Go back to your room.

360
00:17:59,470 --> 00:18:00,250
He Yuanhang, where are you?

361
00:18:02,470 --> 00:18:03,490
I'm working now.

362
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:05,290
I need to work hard

363
00:18:05,310 --> 00:18:06,480
to impress my boss.

364
00:18:06,680 --> 00:18:07,900
That way, I can stay

365
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:08,730
in the criminal department.

366
00:18:08,750 --> 00:18:09,940
Are you trying to get back

367
00:18:09,940 --> 00:18:10,940
to the police station again?

368
00:18:11,790 --> 00:18:12,870
Who says that?

369
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:14,050
That's impossible.

370
00:18:14,070 --> 00:18:15,770
I met Qu Dahai today.

371
00:18:15,790 --> 00:18:16,970
He told me that.

372
00:18:16,990 --> 00:18:18,900
He said you'd return next week.

373
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:19,820
Qu Dahai.

374
00:18:19,990 --> 00:18:20,620
Listen.

375
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:22,580
He's trying to break us up.

376
00:18:22,750 --> 00:18:25,480
He can't wait to return to the police station.

377
00:18:26,330 --> 00:18:26,900
What?

378
00:18:27,160 --> 00:18:28,010
He Yuanhang!

379
00:18:28,030 --> 00:18:28,860
It's noisy here.

380
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:29,980
The lines are mixed up.

381
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:31,370
Officer He said

382
00:18:31,510 --> 00:18:32,770
only six days left till...

383
00:18:33,310 --> 00:18:33,770
Wait.

384
00:18:34,030 --> 00:18:35,100
It's noisy here.

385
00:18:35,230 --> 00:18:37,010
Only six days left till he goes back to...

386
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:38,660
Give me a moment.

387
00:18:44,440 --> 00:18:45,140
Don't worry.

388
00:18:45,360 --> 00:18:47,180
I'll work hard

389
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:48,530
to stay in the criminal department.

390
00:18:49,070 --> 00:18:50,180
I have to hang up now.

391
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:50,860
I have a meeting soon.

392
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:51,580
Okay.

393
00:18:53,120 --> 00:18:54,620
Getting bolder now, huh?

394
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:11,420
Let's go.

395
00:19:12,030 --> 00:19:12,820
You go ahead.

396
00:19:12,840 --> 00:19:13,340
I need to work.

397
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:14,490
Who says it's not about work?

398
00:19:14,750 --> 00:19:15,720
We have a new lead.

399
00:19:16,790 --> 00:19:17,210
Hey!

400
00:19:17,790 --> 00:19:18,380
Wait for me.

401
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:24,380
Where are my shoes?

402
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:30,690
You have five minutes

403
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:32,180
to get yourself some new outfits at the night market.

404
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:41,890
♪Staring at the setting sun, sinking and rising again♪

405
00:19:42,360 --> 00:19:46,370
♪The world remains unchanged, the time remains long♪

406
00:19:46,700 --> 00:19:51,220
♪Traveling the world, the journey is endless♪

407
00:19:51,310 --> 00:19:52,100
Sir, buy some leather shoes.

408
00:19:52,710 --> 00:19:53,620
They are all genuine leather.

409
00:19:53,640 --> 00:19:54,180
Take a look.

410
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:55,210
We have a clearance sale today.

411
00:19:55,230 --> 00:19:56,100
Everything is cheap.

412
00:19:56,120 --> 00:19:56,730
Trust me.

413
00:19:57,230 --> 00:19:57,820
Sir,

414
00:19:57,840 --> 00:19:58,790
you have great taste.

415
00:20:01,230 --> 00:20:02,290
Double Fish Heels.

416
00:20:02,310 --> 00:20:02,970
They are branded.

417
00:20:03,270 --> 00:20:04,050
Are they for your girlfriend?

418
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:07,420
Sir.

419
00:20:08,470 --> 00:20:08,820
Come.

420
00:20:08,840 --> 00:20:09,530
Take a look.

421
00:20:10,230 --> 00:20:11,250
I also have stirrup pants.

422
00:20:11,270 --> 00:20:11,940
Get them too.

423
00:20:12,230 --> 00:20:13,340
Blue and red,

424
00:20:13,360 --> 00:20:13,940
as beautiful as you get.

425
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:18,010
Sir, help me out, will you?

426
00:20:18,030 --> 00:20:19,340
I'll forever remember your generosity.

427
00:20:49,710 --> 00:20:50,340
Did you gain some common sense?

428
00:20:58,680 --> 00:20:59,420
Boat orchids.

429
00:20:59,790 --> 00:21:00,770
You splurged.

430
00:21:02,550 --> 00:21:03,340
It's to compensate someone.

431
00:21:05,710 --> 00:21:06,490
Compensate someone?

432
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:32,010
You're somehow attached

433
00:21:32,030 --> 00:21:33,050
to these old sandals?

434
00:21:36,550 --> 00:21:37,820
It's to compensate someone too.

435
00:21:38,470 --> 00:21:39,580
It's to compensate someone too?

436
00:21:40,160 --> 00:21:41,340
You have only worked for two days.

437
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:42,420
You didn't earn anything,

438
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:43,490
but you have to compensate for losses already.

439
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:45,100
Well done.

440
00:21:54,550 --> 00:21:55,380
Oh.

441
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:56,860
Guess what I saw in the night market.

442
00:21:58,070 --> 00:22:00,100
The blue leather heels worn by the missing woman.

443
00:22:01,030 --> 00:22:02,340
They are called Double Fish Heels.

444
00:22:02,360 --> 00:22:03,490
A renowned brand, apparently.

445
00:22:03,680 --> 00:22:04,290
Expensive too.

446
00:22:04,470 --> 00:22:05,970
They come in different colors.

447
00:22:06,070 --> 00:22:07,860
Red, black,

448
00:22:07,880 --> 00:22:08,900
and even white.

449
00:22:10,270 --> 00:22:11,450
Why didn't you buy something

450
00:22:11,470 --> 00:22:13,380
for your intelligence?

451
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:14,900
Branded goods in a night market?

452
00:22:14,920 --> 00:22:15,970
How authentic can they be?

453
00:22:24,840 --> 00:22:25,250
Hey.

454
00:22:25,270 --> 00:22:25,970
What are you doing?

455
00:22:27,400 --> 00:22:28,340
Don't touch it.

456
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:29,860
If you break it, I'll be in trouble.

457
00:22:33,640 --> 00:22:34,820
Is this your daughter's?

458
00:22:35,880 --> 00:22:36,490
Yes.

459
00:22:37,230 --> 00:22:38,250
How old is she?

460
00:22:40,270 --> 00:22:41,010
Eight years old.

461
00:22:41,470 --> 00:22:42,140
Year 3.

462
00:22:43,510 --> 00:22:45,140
Is she the reason why you don't want

463
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:47,100
to stay in the criminal department?

464
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:50,820
No, it's because of you.

465
00:22:51,510 --> 00:22:52,820
And stop asking questions.

466
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:54,420
It's none of your business.

467
00:22:58,030 --> 00:22:59,380
You studied in Beijing.

468
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:01,050
But you are assigned to Weiyang.

469
00:23:01,070 --> 00:23:02,450
Is your family okay with it?

470
00:23:03,840 --> 00:23:05,050
You checked my file.

471
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:06,940
I didn't.

472
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:07,970
But when Captain Feng

473
00:23:07,990 --> 00:23:08,860
gave me an apprentice,

474
00:23:08,920 --> 00:23:10,140
I had to check what I'd be getting.

475
00:23:10,160 --> 00:23:11,140
Let me reiterate.

476
00:23:11,360 --> 00:23:12,140
I am not your apprentice.

477
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:13,100
All right.

478
00:23:13,840 --> 00:23:14,730
Won't you get sick of nagging,

479
00:23:14,750 --> 00:23:15,530
my dear apprentice?

480
00:23:15,790 --> 00:23:16,210
I...

481
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:25,100
You look so pampered.

482
00:23:25,680 --> 00:23:27,180
Your family must be rich.

483
00:23:28,510 --> 00:23:30,050
What do your parents do?

484
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:50,860
[Shancheng Hotpot]

485
00:24:10,120 --> 00:24:11,150
He's quite handsome,

486
00:24:11,720 --> 00:24:12,770
but his fashion sense

487
00:24:13,230 --> 00:24:14,280
is a bit lacking.

488
00:24:14,710 --> 00:24:16,290
He is dressed like an old man.

489
00:24:21,440 --> 00:24:23,250
I'll bring some drinks over.

490
00:24:25,740 --> 00:24:26,780
What do you want?

491
00:24:27,750 --> 00:24:28,640
Whatever

492
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:29,860
you bring me.

493
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:37,450
I didn't know

494
00:24:37,680 --> 00:24:38,770
it was your number on the poster.

495
00:24:39,270 --> 00:24:40,290
If I had known it,

496
00:24:40,790 --> 00:24:41,290
I wouldn't have called you.

497
00:24:43,470 --> 00:24:45,180
I'm just helping out.

498
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:46,620
Their relatives are eager to find them.

499
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:47,940
Relatives?

500
00:24:57,550 --> 00:24:58,420
Thanks, Cutie.

501
00:24:59,310 --> 00:25:00,490
You're... You're welcome.

502
00:25:04,260 --> 00:25:06,070
[Missing Person]

503
00:25:06,070 --> 00:25:07,210
Do you know them?

504
00:25:12,840 --> 00:25:14,400
The woman on the poster

505
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:16,140
was my colleague.

506
00:25:19,920 --> 00:25:20,970
Colleagues?

507
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:22,580
What's her name?

508
00:25:22,600 --> 00:25:23,770
What kind of work?

509
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:25,970
Ex-colleagues.

510
00:25:26,990 --> 00:25:28,190
Her name is Mengmeng.

511
00:25:28,840 --> 00:25:29,940
What kind of work?

512
00:25:32,750 --> 00:25:33,620
A massage parlor.

513
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:35,050
Oh.

514
00:25:36,160 --> 00:25:37,340
No wonder she used

515
00:25:37,840 --> 00:25:38,580
medical patches.

516
00:25:40,790 --> 00:25:42,250
What's her surname?

517
00:25:42,270 --> 00:25:42,970
Her full name, please.

518
00:25:43,550 --> 00:25:44,730
Mengmeng is just a nickname.

519
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:46,530
Masseuses never use

520
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:48,380
their real names.

521
00:25:49,440 --> 00:25:50,770
Ignore him.

522
00:25:51,070 --> 00:25:52,010
He's just a rookie

523
00:25:52,030 --> 00:25:52,900
who knows nothing.

524
00:25:52,920 --> 00:25:54,860
Just share your information with me.

525
00:25:55,790 --> 00:25:56,650
Cutie.

526
00:25:57,120 --> 00:25:58,180
Let me tell you the truth.

527
00:25:58,710 --> 00:25:59,770
It's a massage parlor,

528
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:01,860
but we do all sorts of things there.

529
00:26:02,030 --> 00:26:03,380
So, the girls there are from

530
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:04,250
other regions.

531
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:05,940
Mengmeng is the only local there.

532
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:07,820
I only know

533
00:26:08,440 --> 00:26:09,250
that her father

534
00:26:09,600 --> 00:26:10,690
is quite sick.

535
00:26:11,360 --> 00:26:12,530
She can't leave Weiyang.

536
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:14,770
Have you seen her father?

537
00:26:16,790 --> 00:26:17,770
I guess it was the guy

538
00:26:17,790 --> 00:26:18,770
she was carrying.

539
00:26:21,230 --> 00:26:23,290
Does Mengmeng have other relatives?

540
00:26:26,710 --> 00:26:28,620
Didn't you tell me her relatives were looking for her?

541
00:26:30,640 --> 00:26:31,970
Police officers and citizens are a family.

542
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:33,620
I can't find her relatives,

543
00:26:34,160 --> 00:26:35,690
but I'll help them find her first.

544
00:26:36,710 --> 00:26:37,340
Officer He.

545
00:26:37,360 --> 00:26:38,660
The police can't find them.

546
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:40,030
Let alone a citizen like me.

547
00:26:45,470 --> 00:26:47,210
Where is

548
00:26:47,230 --> 00:26:47,660
the parlor?

549
00:26:47,990 --> 00:26:48,900
What is the name?

550
00:26:49,120 --> 00:26:50,050
Ask him.

551
00:26:50,680 --> 00:26:51,900
He raided the place.

552
00:26:56,600 --> 00:26:57,380
Pattia.

553
00:26:58,310 --> 00:26:59,100
Cutie.

554
00:26:59,750 --> 00:27:00,860
You've been there before?

555
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:02,660
How come I've never seen you?

556
00:27:02,680 --> 00:27:03,730
No, not at all.

557
00:27:03,750 --> 00:27:04,250
I...

558
00:27:04,750 --> 00:27:05,770
I just came to Weiyang.

559
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:08,340
I just want to know

560
00:27:08,360 --> 00:27:09,420
if Mengmeng

561
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:10,530
is close to anyone else.

562
00:27:11,120 --> 00:27:12,050
She

563
00:27:12,070 --> 00:27:12,820
is the quiet type.

564
00:27:12,990 --> 00:27:13,770
Quite dull.

565
00:27:14,120 --> 00:27:15,420
When she was not working,

566
00:27:15,440 --> 00:27:16,380
she would make small talk with me.

567
00:27:18,510 --> 00:27:19,660
A rich man

568
00:27:19,680 --> 00:27:20,730
often asked for her.

569
00:27:21,270 --> 00:27:22,250
Sometimes,

570
00:27:22,270 --> 00:27:23,250
he would take her with him.

571
00:27:25,470 --> 00:27:26,010
Rich man?

572
00:27:26,360 --> 00:27:27,210
What's his name?

573
00:27:27,600 --> 00:27:28,970
Sun, I think.

574
00:27:29,230 --> 00:27:30,140
I don't know

575
00:27:30,680 --> 00:27:31,820
his name.

576
00:27:34,310 --> 00:27:35,180
Try to recall.

577
00:27:35,400 --> 00:27:36,970
He asked for Mengmeng, not me.

578
00:27:37,550 --> 00:27:38,660
Besides, who uses their real name

579
00:27:38,680 --> 00:27:40,010
in this kind of place?

580
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:43,250
Do you know where Mengmeng

581
00:27:43,270 --> 00:27:44,100
went afterward?

582
00:27:44,750 --> 00:27:45,820
She

583
00:27:46,400 --> 00:27:47,690
went to a foot massage parlor

584
00:27:48,070 --> 00:27:50,010
in Tenglong Street.

585
00:27:50,550 --> 00:27:51,770
I think it's called...

586
00:27:52,200 --> 00:27:53,180
Muse.

587
00:28:13,310 --> 00:28:15,010
People in my line of work

588
00:28:15,510 --> 00:28:16,970
are used to moving frequently.

589
00:28:17,510 --> 00:28:18,580
Many went missing too,

